---
title: One-Pot Cowboy Pork & Bean Chili with Jalapeño & Smoky Red Pepper Crema
description: A good chili has well-seasoned meat, creamy beans, and tender veggies. A great chili, however, has all that and comes together in one pot in under an hour. This chili is one of the greats. And once you take a bite, we can guarantee you’ll agree. Not to mention, these top-notch pork-ified bowls are adorned with some delicious fixings: smoky red pepper crema and sliced jalepeño. If you’ve got some on hand, why not sprinkle some crumbled tortilla chips on top for crunch?
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6372a3e60d45c8098e089f94-0745ee6d.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/65423d45d4ae2bce30667da4.pdf
course: main course
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/one-pot-cowboy-pork-bean-chili-65423d45d4ae2bce30667da4
cuisine: North America
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 740 kcal
  fat: 37 g
  saturated fat: 10 g
  carbohydrates: 57 g
  sugar: 14 g
  protein: 38 g
  fiber: 12 g
  sodium: 1740 mg
time required: 30 minutes
---

Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Thinly slice half the @jalapeño{1} into rounds; mince remaining. TIP: Remove ribs and seeds for less heat.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a large #pot{} over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and as much minced jalapeño as desired. Season with @salt{}. Cook, stirring, until softened, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Add @ground pork{10%ounce} and @Southwest spice blend{2%tablespoon} to pot with scallion mixture; season with salt and @pepper{}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until pork is browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> Ground Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.

Stir @crushed tomatoes{13.76%ounce} and @Tex-Mex paste{1} into pot; cook until warmed through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add @black beans{1} and their liquid, @chicken stock concentrate{2}, @water{1/4%cup}, salt, and pepper; stir to combine. Bring to a simmer and cook until thickened, ~{8-10%minutes}. Turn off heat. (TIP: If chili is too thick, add another splash of water.) Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Divide chili between #bowls{}. Top with @smoky red pepper crema{2%tablespoon}, scallion greens, and as much sliced jalapeño as you like. Serve.